# Resonant Device Firmware (RAK3112)

## Hardware
- RAK3112: ESP32-S3 + SX1262 LoRa, battery-powered, deep-sleep capable
- Dual-core: Core 0 = radio operations, Core 1 = application logic
- Serial1 for debug output (external USB-to-UART), NOT Serial
- ATECC_MOCK=1 currently (mbedTLS software mock for encryption)

## Core Architecture
- `backgroundTasks()` on Core 0: radio init, `resonantRadio.loop()`, ISR handling
- `setup()` + `loop()` on Core 1: app logic, sleep management
- Radio operations use request flags — never call radio hardware from Core 1
- `TxContext` enum tracks transmission purpose to determine post-TX behavior

## Key Patterns
- Always use `ResonantFrame::build*Frame()` for frame construction
- Always use `resonantRadio.send()` for transmission (never touch SX126x directly)
- Always `delete[]` heap-allocated frame/payload buffers after `resonantRadio.send()`
- Encryption: `encryptPayload()` returns iv(12) + ciphertext(N) + tag(16)
- AAD: frameType(1) + senderId(4) + sequenceNumber(4) = 9 bytes
- Sequence numbers start at 1 after adoption, increment per TX

## Wake Cycle
1. Wake from deep sleep → setup() → init storage, encryption, radio
2. Check adoption state → if unadopted: advertise → listen for request
3. If adopted: encrypt telemetry → send to parent → wait for ACK → sleep
4. First boot: send metrics frame after telemetry ACK

## Build & Deploy
```
pio run -t upload          # compile and flash
pio run -t monitor         # serial monitor (115200 baud)
pio run -t upload && pio run -t monitor  # both
```
Upload port: /dev/cu.SLAB_USBtoUART
